137
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:36,149
The elevator.

138
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:42,558
Oh, shit!

139
00:13:47,040 --> 00:13:48,109
What do they want?

140
00:13:48,280 --> 00:13:51,556
I don 't know. If you don 't want
to find out, get out of there.

141
00:13:51,720 --> 00:13:52,709
How?

142
00:13:52,880 --> 00:13:55,838
I can guide you,
but you must do exactly as I say.

143
00:13:56,680 --> 00:13:58,591
The cubicle across from you is empty.

144
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:03,636
-But what if they--
-Go. Now.

145
00:14:10,120 --> 00:14:12,395
Stay here for just a moment.

146
00:14:19,320 --> 00:14:21,959
When I tell you,
go to the end of the row...

147
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:24,077
... to the office
at the end of the hall.

148
00:14:24,320 --> 00:14:26,595
Stay as low as you can.

149
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:29,869
Go. Now.

150
00:14:43,680 --> 00:14:47,070
Good. Now, outside
there is a scaffold.

151
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:51,910
-How do you know this?
- We don 't have time.

152
00:14:52,160 --> 00:14:54,879
To your left there 's a window.
Go to it.

153
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:58,519
Open it.

154
00:14:59,320 --> 00:15:01,038
Take the scaffold to the roof.

155
00:15:01,280 --> 00:15:03,748
No way! No way!
This is crazy!

156
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:06,275
There are two ways
out of this building.

157
00:15:06,520 --> 00:15:10,149
One is that scaffold.
The other is in their custody.

158
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:13,472
You take a chance either way.
I leave it to you.

159
00:15:16,920 --> 00:15:18,592
This is insane!

160
00:15:19,720 --> 00:15:21,517
Why is this happening to me?

161
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:23,358
What'd I do?

162
00:15:23,720 --> 00:15:26,359
I' m nobody.
I didn't do anything.

163
00:15:26,920 --> 00:15:28,319
I' m gonna die.

164
00:15:37,720 --> 00:15:38,709
Shit!

165
00:15:58,160 --> 00:15:59,229
Oh, shit!

166
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:05,718
I can't do this.

167
00:16:17,800 --> 00:16:18,835
Shit.

168
00:17:06,080 --> 00:17:10,710
As you can see, we've had our eye
on you for some time now, Mr. Anderson.

169
00:17:11,960 --> 00:17:14,520
It seems that you've been living...

170
00:17:14,760 --> 00:17:16,796
...two lives.

171
00:17:18,160 --> 00:17:20,549
In one life,
you're Thomas A. Anderson...

172
00:17:20,800 --> 00:17:23,997
...program writer for
a respectable software company.

173
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:28,151
You have a social security number.
You pay your taxes.

174
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:29,794
And you...

175
00:17:31,320 --> 00:17:34,790
...help your landlady
carry out her garbage.

176
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:40,192
The other life is lived in computers...

177
00:17:40,480 --> 00:17:43,313
...where you go by
the hacker alias "Neo"...

178
00:17:43,560 --> 00:17:48,156
...and are guilty of virtually every
computer crime we have a law for.

179
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:51,277
One of these lives...

180
00:17:51,520 --> 00:17:53,272
...has a future.

181
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:55,511
And one of them does not.

182
00:17:59,080 --> 00:18:02,755
I'm going to be as forthcoming
as I can be, Mr. Anderson.

183
00:18:03,720 --> 00:18:04,994
You're here...

184
00:18:05,320 --> 00:18:07,470
...because we need your help.

185
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:13,838
We know that you've been contacted
by a certain...

186
00:18:14,080 --> 00:18:15,798
...individual.

187
00:18:16,680 --> 00:18:20,559
A man who calls himself "Morpheus. "

188
00:18:21,520 --> 00:18:25,354
Whatever you think you know
about this man is irrelevant.

189
00:18:25,600 --> 00:18:27,909
He is considered by many authorities...

190
00:18:28,160 --> 00:18:31,072
...to be the most dangerous man alive.

191
00:18:33,720 --> 00:18:34,869
My colleagues...

192
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:38,078
...believe that I am wasting
my time with you.

193
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:41,636
But I believe you wish
to do the right thing.

194
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:45,276
We're willing to wipe the slate clean...

195
00:18:45,640 --> 00:18:47,676
...give you a fresh start.

196
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:50,958
All we're asking in return
is your cooperation...

197
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:54,556
...in bringing
a known terrorist to justice.

198
00:18:55,880 --> 00:18:57,074
Yeah.

199
00:18:58,320 --> 00:19:00,311
That sounds like a really good deal.

200
00:19:01,880 --> 00:19:03,552
But I got a better one.

201
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:05,233
How about...

202
00:19:05,640 --> 00:19:07,551
...I give you the finger...

203
00:19:10,040 --> 00:19:11,996
...and you give me my phone call.

204
00:19:14,080 --> 00:19:15,832
Mr. Anderson...

205
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:20,834
...you disappoint me.

206
00:19:21,080 --> 00:19:23,594
You can't scare me
with this gestapo crap.

207
00:19:23,840 --> 00:19:25,159
I know my rights.

208
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:26,833
I want my phone call.

209
00:19:27,400 --> 00:19:29,470
Tell me, Mr. Anderson...

210
00:19:30,320 --> 00:19:31,673
...what good is a phone call...

211
00:19:31,920 --> 00:19:35,356
...if you're unable to speak?

212
00:20:07,760 --> 00:20:09,876
You're going to help us,
Mr. Anderson...

213
00:20:10,560 --> 00:20:12,551
...whether you want to or not.

214
00:21:08,480 --> 00:21:11,597
This line is tapped,
so I must be brief.

215
00:21:11,840 --> 00:21:15,958
They got to you first, but they've
underestimated how important you are.

216
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:17,952
If they knew what I know...

217
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:20,111
... you would probably be dead.

218
00:21:21,080 --> 00:21:24,629
What are you talking about?
What is happening to me?

219
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:29,510
You are the One, Neo. You may have
spent the last few years...

220
00:21:29,760 --> 00:21:32,593
...Iooking for me, but I've spent
my entire life...

221
00:21:32,840 --> 00:21:34,273
...Iooking for you.

222
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:37,830
Now, do you still want to meet?

223
00:21:38,760 --> 00:21:41,513
-Y es.
- Then go to the Adams Street bridge.

224
00:21:51,320 --> 00:21:52,469
Get in.

225
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:07,710
-What's this?
-It's necessary, Neo. For our protection.

226
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:10,030
-From what?
-From you.

227
00:22:11,520 --> 00:22:12,919
T ake off your shirt.

228
00:22:13,240 --> 00:22:15,117
Stop the car.

229
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:19,715
Listen, coppertop.

230
00:22:19,960 --> 00:22:21,871
We don't have time for 20 Questions.

231
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:24,635
Right now, there's only one rule:

232
00:22:24,920 --> 00:22:26,194
Our way...

233
00:22:26,520 --> 00:22:27,555
...or the highway.

234
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:34,869
Fine.

235
00:22:36,680 --> 00:22:39,035
Please, Neo, you have to trust me.

236
00:22:39,600 --> 00:22:42,114
-Why?
-Because you have been down there.

237
00:22:42,840 --> 00:22:43,989
You know that road.

238
00:22:44,960 --> 00:22:46,552
You know exactly where it ends.

239
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:50,790
And I know that's
not where you want to be.

240
00:23:04,400 --> 00:23:05,879
Apoc, lights.

241
00:23:08,280 --> 00:23:10,350
Lie back.
Lift up your shirt.

242
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:14,350
-What's that?
-You're bugged.

243
00:23:21,800 --> 00:23:23,199
Try and relax.

244
00:23:29,240 --> 00:23:30,355
Come on.

245
00:23:31,520 --> 00:23:33,476
Come on.

246
00:23:34,080 --> 00:23:36,036
It's on the move.

247
00:23:36,720 --> 00:23:37,869
Come on, you shit.

248
00:23:39,640 --> 00:23:41,631
-You're gonna lose it.
-No, I'm not.

249
00:23:41,800 --> 00:23:42,994
Clear!

250
