Jesus Christ!
That thing's real?!

251
00:24:25,640 --> 00:24:26,914
This is it.

252
00:24:30,120 --> 00:24:32,475
Let me give you one piece of advice.

253
00:24:33,400 --> 00:24:34,992
Be honest.

254
00:24:36,520 --> 00:24:38,636
He knows more than you can imagine.

255
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:48,274
At last.

256
00:24:49,760 --> 00:24:50,795
Welcome, Neo.

257
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:53,791
As you no doubt have guessed...

258
00:24:54,040 --> 00:24:55,234
...I am Morpheus.

259
00:24:56,240 --> 00:24:57,753
It's an honor to meet you.

260
00:24:58,200 --> 00:24:59,189
No...

261
00:24:59,760 --> 00:25:00,988
...the honor is mine.

262
00:25:01,880 --> 00:25:04,269
Please, come. Sit.

263
00:25:18,760 --> 00:25:20,318
I imagine...

264
00:25:20,720 --> 00:25:23,359
...that right now you're feeling
a bit like Alice...

265
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:27,309
...tumbling down the rabbit hole?

266
00:25:28,200 --> 00:25:29,872
You could say that.

267
00:25:30,040 --> 00:25:32,554
I can see it in your eyes.

268
00:25:33,120 --> 00:25:36,271
You have the look of a man
who accepts what he sees...

269
00:25:36,520 --> 00:25:38,670
...because he's expecting to wake up.

270
00:25:40,040 --> 00:25:42,554
Ironically, this is not
far from the truth.

271
00:25:43,200 --> 00:25:45,589
Do you believe in fate, Neo?

272
00:25:45,880 --> 00:25:48,075
-No.
-Why not?

273
00:25:48,320 --> 00:25:50,993
I don't like the idea that
I'm not in control of my life.

274
00:25:52,040 --> 00:25:55,237
I know exactly what you mean.

275
00:25:59,360 --> 00:26:01,635
Let me tell you why you're here.

276
00:26:02,640 --> 00:26:04,119
You know something.

277
00:26:04,640 --> 00:26:06,198
What you know,
you can't explain.

278
00:26:06,680 --> 00:26:08,193
But you feel it.

279
00:26:08,760 --> 00:26:10,591
You felt it your entire life.

280
00:26:11,160 --> 00:26:15,153
Something's wrong with the world.
You don't know what, but it's there.

281
00:26:15,640 --> 00:26:17,756
Like a splinter in your mind...

282
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:19,797
...driving you mad.

283
00:26:20,680 --> 00:26:23,319
It is this feeling
that has brought you to me.

284
00:26:25,760 --> 00:26:27,512
Do you know what
I'm talking about?

285
00:26:29,280 --> 00:26:30,554
The Matrix?

286
00:26:32,960 --> 00:26:34,552
Do you want to know...

287
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:36,911
...what it is?

288
00:26:39,200 --> 00:26:40,997
The Matrix is everywhere.

289
00:26:41,240 --> 00:26:42,878
It is all around us.

290
00:26:43,120 --> 00:26:44,997
Even now, in this very room.

291
00:26:45,800 --> 00:26:47,916
You can see it when you
look out your window...

292
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:50,390
...or when you turn on your television.

293
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:53,234
You can feel it when you go to work...

294
00:26:54,720 --> 00:26:56,312
...when you go to church...

295
00:26:56,720 --> 00:26:58,711
...when you pay your taxes.

296
00:26:59,800 --> 00:27:02,598
It is the world that has been
pulled over your eyes...

297
00:27:02,840 --> 00:27:04,353
...to blind you from the truth.

298
00:27:06,480 --> 00:27:07,674
What truth?

299
00:27:11,760 --> 00:27:13,239
That you are a slave.

300
00:27:14,680 --> 00:27:16,875
Like everyone else,
you were born into bondage...

301
00:27:17,120 --> 00:27:21,591
... born into a prison that you cannot
smell or taste or touch.

302
00:27:21,880 --> 00:27:23,108
A prison...

303
00:27:23,360 --> 00:27:24,475
...for your mind.

304
00:27:31,160 --> 00:27:33,390
Unfortunately, no one can be...

305
00:27:33,720 --> 00:27:35,995
...told what the Matrix is.

306
00:27:39,320 --> 00:27:41,117
You have to see it for yourself.

307
00:27:50,240 --> 00:27:52,435
This is your last chance.

308
00:27:52,680 --> 00:27:54,910
After this, there is no turning back.

309
00:27:55,360 --> 00:27:56,793
You take the blue pill...

310
00:27:57,080 --> 00:27:59,992
...the story ends, you wake up
in your bed and believe...

311
00:28:00,240 --> 00:28:01,958
...whatever you want to believe.

312
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:03,474
You take the red pill...

313
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:05,597
...you stay in Wonderland...

314
00:28:06,080 --> 00:28:08,674
...and I show you how deep
the rabbit hole goes.

315
00:28:18,160 --> 00:28:19,309
Remember...

316
00:28:20,120 --> 00:28:23,032
...all I'm offering is the truth.
Nothing more.

317
00:28:36,760 --> 00:28:38,034
Follow me.

318
00:28:40,480 --> 00:28:42,072
Apoc, are we on-line?

319
00:28:42,320 --> 00:28:43,639
Almost.

320
00:28:46,840 --> 00:28:48,796
Time is always against us.

321
00:28:49,160 --> 00:28:50,593
Please take a seat there.

322
00:29:08,040 --> 00:29:09,678
You did all this?

323
00:29:13,640 --> 00:29:15,551
The pill you took is
part of a trace program.

324
00:29:16,280 --> 00:29:20,717
It disrupts your carrier signals
so we can pinpoint your location.

325
00:29:21,240 --> 00:29:22,229
What does that mean?

326
00:29:22,800 --> 00:29:24,870
It means buckle your
seat belt, Dorothy...

327
00:29:25,200 --> 00:29:26,474
...because Kansas...

328
00:29:26,720 --> 00:29:27,709
...is going bye-bye.

329
00:30:04,080 --> 00:30:05,399
Did you...?

330
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:19,873
Have you ever had a dream, Neo,
that you were so sure was real?

331
00:30:21,280 --> 00:30:23,748
What if you were unable
to wake from that dream?

332
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:26,389
How would you know the difference
between the dream world...

333
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:28,353
...and the real world?

334
00:30:29,920 --> 00:30:32,195
-This can't be.
-Be what?

335
00:30:32,880 --> 00:30:34,313
Be real?

336
00:30:38,120 --> 00:30:39,348
Going into replication.

337
00:30:39,800 --> 00:30:42,360
-Still nothing.
-It's cold.

338
00:30:42,600 --> 00:30:43,919
It's cold!

339
00:30:47,640 --> 00:30:49,232
Tank, we'll need a signal soon.

340
00:30:50,720 --> 00:30:53,234
-I got a fibrillation.
-Apoc, location.

341
00:30:53,480 --> 00:30:54,879
Targeting almost there.

342
00:30:58,040 --> 00:30:59,393
He's going into arrest.

343
00:30:59,640 --> 00:31:02,029
-Lock. I got him!
-Now, Tank, now!

344
00:33:52,040 --> 00:33:53,075
Welcome...

345
00:33:53,400 --> 00:33:55,231
...to the real world.

346
00:33:56,600 --> 00:33:58,352
We've done it, Trinity.

347
00:33:58,600 --> 00:34:00,079
We found him.

348
00:34:00,320 --> 00:34:02,993
-I hope you're right.
-I don't have to hope.

349
00:34:03,560 --> 00:34:05,073
I know it.

350
00:34:10,040 --> 00:34:11,029
Am I dead?

351
00:34:11,520 --> 00:34:13,590
Far from it.

352
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:28,353
He still needs a lot of work.

353
00:34:29,840 --> 00:34:30,875
What are you doing?

354
00:34:31,120 --> 00:34:33,236
Your muscles atrophied.
We're rebuilding them.

355
00:34:33,800 --> 00:34:35,279
Why do my eyes hurt?

356
00:34:35,960 --> 00:34:37,757
You've never used them before.

357
00:34:41,560 --> 00:34:44,199
Rest, Neo. The answers are coming.

358
00:35:55,720 --> 00:35:57,233
Morpheus, what's happened to me?

359
00:35:57,960 --> 00:36:01,669
-What is this place?
-More important than "what" is "when. "

360
00:36:02,360 --> 00:36:05,318
-When?
-You believe it's the year 1 999...

361
00:36:05,560 --> 00:36:07,710
...when in fact, it's closer to 21 99.

362
00:36:08,800 --> 00:36:11,439
I can't tell you exactly
what year it is...

363
00:36:11,680 --> 00:36:13,238
...because we honestly don't know.

364
00:36:13,720 --> 00:36:16,439
There's nothing I can say
that will explain it for you.

365
00:36:16,680 --> 00:36:17,795
Come with me.

366
00:36:18,080 --> 00:36:19,308
See for yourself.

367
00:36:19,840 --> 00:36:21,512
This is my ship.

368
00:36:21,800 --> 00:36:24,598
The Nebuchadnezzar.
It's a hovercraft.

369
00:36:27,320 --> 00:36:28,992
This is the main deck.

370
00:36:34,600 --> 00:36:35,715
This is the core...

371
00:36:38,120 --> 00:36:41,715
...where we broadcast our pirate signal
and hack into the Matrix.

372
00:36:44,960 --> 00:36:47,997
Most of my crew you already know.

373
00:36:52,800 --> 00:36:54,153
This is Apoc...

374
00:36:54,920 --> 00:36:56,194
...Switch...

375
00:36:57,720 --> 00:36:58,835
...and Cypher.

376
00:36:59,080 --> 00:37:02,629
The ones you don't know:
Tank and his big brother, Dozer.

377
00:37:03,480 --> 00:37:05,789
The little one behind you is Mouse.

378
00:37:09,960 --> 00:37:13,077
You wanted to know
what the Matrix is?

379
00:37:14,080 --> 00:37:15,229
Trinity.

380
00:37:35,400 --> 00:37:36,913
Try to relax.

381
00:37:41,600 --> 00:37:43,352
This will feel a little weird.

382
00:37:54,840 --> 00:37:55,955
This...

383
00:37:56,320 --> 00:37:57,958
...is the Construct.

384
00:37:58,360 --> 00:38:00,396
It's our loading program.

385
00:38:00,640 --> 00:38:02,995
We can load anything, from clothing...

386
00:38:03,240 --> 00:38:04,559
...to equipment...

387
00:38:04,840 --> 00:38:06,114
...weapons...

388
00:38:06,720 --> 00:38:08,472
...training simulations...

389
00:38:08,840 --> 00:38:11,274
...anything we need.

390
00:38:13,960 --> 00:38:16,269
Right now we're inside
a computer program?

391
00:38:16,560 --> 00:38:18,391
Is it really so hard to believe?

392
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:21,394
Your clothes are different.
The plugs in your body are gone.

393
00:38:22,560 --> 00:38:24,551
Your hair has changed.

394
00:38:24,920 --> 00:38:28,117
Your appearance now is what we call
"residual self-image. "

395
00:38:28,800 --> 00:38:31,314
It is the mental projection
of your digital self.

396
00:38:36,960 --> 00:38:38,029
This isn't real?

397
00:38:38,280 --> 00:38:39,759
What is "real"?

398
00:38:40,120 --> 00:38:42,270
How do you define "real"?

399
00:38:42,560 --> 00:38:44,391
If you're talking about
what you can feel...

400
00:38:44,640 --> 00:38:46,949
...what you can smell, taste and see...

401
00:38:47,200 --> 00:38:50,909
...then "real" is simply electrical
signals interpreted by your brain.

402
00:38:54,920 --> 00:38:57,229
This is the world that you know.

403
00:38:58,600 --> 00:39:01,512
The world as it was at the end
of the 20th century.

404
00:39:03,800 --> 00:39:07,952
It exists now only as part of
a neural-interactive simulation...

405
00:39:08,200 --> 00:39:09,394
...that we call the Matrix.

406
00:39:13,760 --> 00:39:16,479
You've been living
in a dream world, Neo.

407
00:39:17,400 --> 00:39:18,469
This is the world...

408
00:39:18,760 --> 00:39:20,478
...as it exists today.

409
00:39:32,960 --> 00:39:35,793
Welcome to "the desert...

410
00:39:36,640 --> 00:39:38,153
...of the real. "

411
00:39:41,400 --> 00:39:43,675
We have only bits and pieces
of information.

412
00:39:43,920 --> 00:39:47,549
But what we know for certain
is that in the early 21 st century...

413
00:39:47,800 --> 00:39:50,917
...all of mankind was united
in celebration.

414
00:39:51,160 --> 00:39:55,711
We marveled at our own magnificence
as we gave birth to Al.

415
00:39:56,480 --> 00:39:57,549
Al.

416
00:39:58,560 --> 00:39:59,879
You mean artificial intelligence.

417
00:40:00,120 --> 00:40:04,352
A singular consciousness that spawned
an entire race of machines.

418
00:40:05,160 --> 00:40:08,470
We don't know who struck first,
us or them.

419
00:40:08,880 --> 00:40:11,952
But we know that it was us
that scorched the sky.

420
00:40:13,560 --> 00:40:15,630
They were dependent on solar power...

421
00:40:15,880 --> 00:40:19,077
...and it was believed that
they would be unable to survive...

422
00:40:19,400 --> 00:40:22,756
...without an energy source
as abundant as the sun.

423
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:27,676
Throughout human history, we have been
dependent on machines to survive.

424
00:40:29,080 --> 00:40:33,119
Fate, it seems, is not
without a sense of irony.

425
00:40:36,200 --> 00:40:40,432
The human body generates more
bioelectricity than a 1 20-volt battery.

426
00:40:40,680 --> 00:40:44,639
And over 25,000 BTUs of body heat.

427
00:40:46,480 --> 00:40:48,550
Combined with a form of fusion...

428
00:40:48,880 --> 00:40:53,510
...the machines had found all the energy
they would ever need.

429
00:40:57,400 --> 00:41:00,995
There are fields, Neo,
endless fields...

430
00:41:01,240 --> 00:41:04,357
...where human beings
are no longer born.

431
00:41:05,040 --> 00:41:06,792
We are grown.

432
00:41:12,600 --> 00:41:15,068
For the longest time,
I wouldn't believe it.

433
00:41:15,320 --> 00:41:17,880
And then I saw the fields
with my own eyes...

434
00:41:19,160 --> 00:41:20,718
...watched them liquefy the dead...

435
00:41:20,960 --> 00:41:24,157
...so they could be fed intravenously
to the living.

436
00:41:24,680 --> 00:41:28,753
And standing there,
facing the pure, horrifying precision...

437
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:31,798
...I came to realize
the obviousness of the truth.

438
00:41:34,320 --> 00:41:36,038
What is the Matrix?

439
00:41:37,200 --> 00:41:38,189
Control.

440
00:41:39,520 --> 00:41:42,751
The Matrix is a computer-generated
dream world...

441
00:41:43,520 --> 00:41:46,478
... built to keep us under control...

442
00:41:47,600 --> 00:41:50,637
...in order to change a human being...

443
00:41:51,240 --> 00:41:52,355
...into this.

444
00:41:53,680 --> 00:41:54,749
No.

445
00:41:56,320 --> 00:41:57,833
I don't believe it.

446
00:41:58,200 --> 00:41:59,349
It's not possible.

447
00:41:59,920 --> 00:42:04,311
I didn't say it would be easy, Neo.
I just said it would be the truth.

448
00:42:04,560 --> 00:42:06,073
Stop!

449
00:42:06,320 --> 00:42:07,469
Let me out!

450
00:42:08,160 --> 00:42:09,991
Let me out! I want out!

451
00:42:11,880 --> 00:42:14,440
-Easy, Neo. Easy.
-Get this thing out of me.

452
00:42:14,680 --> 00:42:16,272
Get this thing out of me!

453
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:19,433
Don't touch me!

454
00:42:19,680 --> 00:42:21,238
Stay away from me!

455
00:42:21,640 --> 00:42:23,073
I don't believe it.

456
00:42:23,760 --> 00:42:24,909
I don't believe it.

457
00:42:25,160 --> 00:42:26,673
I don't believe it.

458
00:42:26,840 --> 00:42:30,196
-He's gonna pop.
-Breathe, Neo. Just breathe.

459
00:42:47,840 --> 00:42:49,558
I can't go back, can l?

460
00:42:50,120 --> 00:42:51,394
No.

461
00:42:52,520 --> 00:42:53,669
But if you could...

462
00:42:54,480 --> 00:42:55,913
...would you really want to?

463
00:42:58,320 --> 00:42:59,673
I owe you an apology.

464
00:43:00,200 --> 00:43:01,519
We have a rule.

465
00:43:01,960 --> 00:43:05,191
We never free a mind
once it's reached a certain age.

466
00:43:05,440 --> 00:43:08,591
It's dangerous.
The mind has trouble letting go.

467
00:43:08,840 --> 00:43:11,035
I've seen it before, and I'm sorry.

468
00:43:12,040 --> 00:43:14,031
I did what I did because...

469
00:43:14,720 --> 00:43:16,119
...I had to.

470
00:43:24,200 --> 00:43:28,113
When the Matrix was first built,
there was a man born inside...

471
00:43:28,600 --> 00:43:32,229
...who had the ability
to change whatever he wanted...

472
00:43:32,600 --> 00:43:35,398
...to remake the Matrix as he saw fit.

473
00:43:37,080 --> 00:43:40,390
It was he who freed the first of us...

474
00:43:41,240 --> 00:43:42,798
...taught us the truth.

475
00:43:44,200 --> 00:43:47,158
As long as the Matrix exists...

476
00:43:47,480 --> 00:43:49,471
...the human race will never be free.

477
00:43:53,520 --> 00:43:54,999
After he died...

478
00:43:55,720 --> 00:43:58,314
...the Oracle prophesied his return...

479
00:43:58,840 --> 00:44:01,912
...and that his coming would hail
the destruction of the Matrix...

480
00:44:02,160 --> 00:44:03,752
...end the war...

481
00:44:04,080 --> 00:44:05,229
...bring freedom to our people.

482
00:44:06,560 --> 00:44:10,997
That is why there are those of us who
spent our lives searching the Matrix...

483
00:44:11,320 --> 00:44:12,833
...Iooking for him.

484
00:44:15,160 --> 00:44:17,151
I did what I did because...

485
00:44:18,720 --> 00:44:20,756
...I believe that search is over.

486
00:44:25,640 --> 00:44:26,993
Get some rest.

487
00:44:27,600 --> 00:44:29,318
You're going to need it.

488
00:44:31,960 --> 00:44:33,837
For what?

489
00:44:35,880 --> 00:44:36,995
Your training.

490
00:44:54,560 --> 00:44:56,198
Morning. Did you sleep?

491
00:44:57,040 --> 00:44:58,189
You will tonight.

492
00:44:58,560 --> 00:45:00,039
I guarantee it.

493
00:45:01,480 --> 00:45:03,311
I'm Tank. I'll be your operator.

494
00:45:03,760 --> 00:45:06,069
-You don't have any--
-Holes? Nope.

495
00:45:06,960 --> 00:45:11,476
Me and my brother, Dozer, are 1 00% pure,
old-fashioned, homegrown human.

496
00:45:11,720 --> 00:45:12,869
Born free right here...

497
00:45:13,400 --> 00:45:14,674
...in the real world.

498
00:45:14,920 --> 00:45:16,512
Genuine child of Zion.

499
00:45:17,320 --> 00:45:19,675
-Zion?
-lf the war was over tomorrow...

500
00:45:19,920 --> 00:45:21,273
...Zion's where the party would be.

501
00:45:21,760 --> 00:45:22,988
It's a city?

502
00:45:23,240 --> 00:45:26,277
The last human city.
The only place we have left.

503
00:45:27,800 --> 00:45:28,994
Where is it?

504
00:45:30,320 --> 00:45:31,639
Deep underground...

505
00:45:31,880 --> 00:45:33,950
...near the Earth's core,
where it's still warm.

506
00:45:35,520 --> 00:45:37,317
You live long enough,
you might see it.

507
00:45:39,480 --> 00:45:44,110
Goddamn! I gotta tell you, I'm excited
to see what you're capable of...

508
00:45:44,360 --> 00:45:46,032
...if Morpheus is right and all.

509
00:45:46,520 --> 00:45:49,159
We're not supposed to
talk about this, but...

510
00:45:49,400 --> 00:45:50,753
...if you are...

511
00:45:51,800 --> 00:45:53,711
...it's a very exciting time.

512
00:45:54,720 --> 00:45:57,314
We got a lot to do.
We gotta get to it.

513
00:46:01,080 --> 00:46:03,878
We're supposed to start
with these programs first.

514
00:46:04,840 --> 00:46:08,150
That's major boring shit.
Let's do something more fun.

515
00:46:08,480 --> 00:46:09,913
How about...

516
00:46:11,400 --> 00:46:13,072
...combat training?

517
00:46:18,880 --> 00:46:20,279
"Jujitsu"?

518
00:46:21,120 --> 00:46:22,712
I'm going to learn jujitsu?

519
00:46:33,600 --> 00:46:34,749
Holy shit!

520
00:46:35,000 --> 00:46:37,230
"Hey, Mikey, I think he likes it. "

521
00:46:37,560 --> 00:46:38,788
How about some more?

522
00:46:39,040 --> 00:46:40,268
Hell, yes.

523
00:46:42,200 --> 00:46:43,269
Hell, yeah.

524
00:46:54,880 --> 00:46:55,995
How is he?

525
00:46:56,240 --> 00:46:58,356
Ten hours straight.
He's a machine.

526
00:47:09,080 --> 00:47:10,399
I know kung fu.

527
00:47:12,000 --> 00:47:12,989
Show me.

528
00:47:14,680 --> 00:47:16,352
This is a sparring program...

529
00:47:16,600 --> 00:47:19,273
...similar to the programmed reality
of the Matrix.

530
00:47:19,520 --> 00:47:21,750
It has the same basic rules.
Like gravity.

531
00:47:22,000 --> 00:47:25,310
These rules are no different
than those of a computer system.

532
00:47:25,840 --> 00:47:27,273
Some of them can be bent.

533
00:47:27,480 --> 00:47:29,835
Others can be broken.

534
00:47:30,200 --> 00:47:31,394
Understand?

535
00:47:32,640 --> 00:47:35,074
Then hit me, if you can.

536
00:48:12,360 --> 00:48:13,475
Good!

537
00:48:14,200 --> 00:48:15,315
Adaptation.

538
00:48:15,600 --> 00:48:16,749
Improvisation.

539
00:48:17,040 --> 00:48:18,314
But your weakness...

540
00:48:18,560 --> 00:48:19,879
...is not your technique.

541
00:48:26,560 --> 00:48:28,551
Morpheus is fighting Neo.

542
00:49:37,880 --> 00:49:38,995
How did I beat you?

543
00:49:45,320 --> 00:49:46,355
You're too fast.

544
00:49:46,880 --> 00:49:48,154
Do you believe that...

545
00:49:48,520 --> 00:49:50,909
...my being stronger or faster...

546
00:49:51,160 --> 00:49:54,675
...has anything to do
with my muscles in this place?

547
00:49:58,560 --> 00:50:00,278
You think you're breathing air?

548
00:50:13,240 --> 00:50:14,389
Again!

549
00:50:25,400 --> 00:50:27,709
Jesus Christ, he's fast!

550
00:50:27,960 --> 00:50:30,076
His neuro-kinetics
are way above normal.

551
00:50:35,320 --> 00:50:36,719
What are you waiting for?

552
00:50:36,960 --> 00:50:38,837
You're faster than this.

553
00:50:40,960 --> 00:50:43,076
Don't think you are.

554
00:50:43,320 --> 00:50:44,912
Know you are.

555
00:50:54,880 --> 00:50:57,599
Come on! Stop trying to hit me,
and hit me!

556
00:51:07,080 --> 00:51:08,752
I don't believe it.

557
00:51:10,240 --> 00:51:12,276
I know what you're trying to do.

558
00:51:13,880 --> 00:51:15,950
I'm trying to free your mind, Neo.

559
00:51:16,280 --> 00:51:18,271
But I can only show you the door.

560
00:51:18,840 --> 00:51:20,637
You have to walk through it.

561
00:51:22,880 --> 00:51:24,916
Tank, load the jump program.

562
00:51:36,040 --> 00:51:38,634
You have to let it all go, Neo.
Fear...

563
00:51:39,160 --> 00:51:41,230
...doubt and disbelief.

564
00:51:42,360 --> 00:51:44,954
Free your mind.

565
00:52:00,480 --> 00:52:02,118
Okey-dokey.

566
00:52:04,120 --> 00:52:05,235
Free my mind.

567
00:52:05,680 --> 00:52:06,749
What if he makes it?

568
00:52:07,000 --> 00:52:09,594
-No one's ever made their first jump.
-I know.

569
00:52:10,880 --> 00:52:13,235
-But what if he does?
-He won't.

570
00:52:13,720 --> 00:52:14,835
Come on.

571
00:52:15,080 --> 00:52:16,195
All right.

572
00:52:16,640 --> 00:52:18,596
No problem. Free my mind.

573
00:52:19,360 --> 00:52:22,033
Free my mind. No problem. Right.

574
00:52:40,640 --> 00:52:42,232
What does that mean?

575
00:52:42,600 --> 00:52:44,352
It doesn't mean anything.

576
00:52:44,920 --> 00:52:47,388
Everybody falls the first time.

577
00:52:47,840 --> 00:52:49,068
Right, Trin?

578
00:53:08,920 --> 00:53:11,434
-I thought it wasn't real.
-Your mind makes it real.

579
00:53:14,560 --> 00:53:16,710
If you're killed in the Matrix...

580
00:53:16,880 --> 00:53:17,869
...you die here?

581
00:53:18,480 --> 00:53:20,835
The body cannot live without the mind.

582
00:53:50,080 --> 00:53:53,311
I don't remember you ever
bringing me dinner.

583
00:53:56,280 --> 00:53:58,999
There is something about him,
isn't there?

584
00:53:59,600 --> 00:54:01,158
You're a believer now?

585
00:54:02,120 --> 00:54:03,269
I keep wondering...

586
00:54:03,520 --> 00:54:07,035
...if Morpheus is so sure,
why not take him to see the Oracle?

587
00:54:07,920 --> 00:54:10,718
Morpheus will take him
when he's ready.

588
00:54:20,120 --> 00:54:21,599
The Matrix is a system, Neo.

589
00:54:23,280 --> 00:54:24,508
That system is our enemy.

590
00:54:25,120 --> 00:54:27,350
But when you're inside,
what do you see?

591
00:54:27,600 --> 00:54:31,229
Businessmen, teachers,
lawyers, carpenters.

592
00:54:31,680 --> 00:54:34,148
The very minds of the people
we are trying to save.

593
00:54:34,400 --> 00:54:37,233
But until we do, these people are
a part of that system...

594
00:54:37,480 --> 00:54:40,631
...and that makes them our enemy.
You have to understand...

595
00:54:40,880 --> 00:54:44,077
... most of these people are not
ready to be unplugged.

596
00:54:44,320 --> 00:54:45,833
And many of them are so inert...

597
00:54:46,080 --> 00:54:48,389
...so hopelessly dependent
on the system...

598
00:54:48,640 --> 00:54:51,234
...that they will fight to protect it.

599
00:54:52,680 --> 00:54:56,275
Were you listening to me or looking
at the woman in the red dress?

600
00:54:57,120 --> 00:54:58,109
Look again.

601
00:54:59,320 --> 00:55:00,355
Freeze it.

602
00:55:06,720 --> 00:55:08,278
This isn't the Matrix?

603
00:55:10,000 --> 00:55:13,675
It's another training program
designed to teach you one thing:

604
00:55:14,280 --> 00:55:16,589
If you are not one of us,
you are one of them.

605
00:55:17,120 --> 00:55:19,793
-What are they?
-Sentient programs.

606
00:55:20,520 --> 00:55:24,638
They can move in and out of any software
still hardwired to their system.

607
00:55:25,000 --> 00:55:28,231
That means that anyone
we haven't unplugged...

608
00:55:28,560 --> 00:55:29,834
...is potentially an agent.

609
00:55:30,760 --> 00:55:32,512
Inside the Matrix...

610
00:55:33,080 --> 00:55:34,718
...they are everyone...

611
00:55:35,040 --> 00:55:36,678
...and they are no one.

612
00:55:36,920 --> 00:55:39,912
We have survived by hiding
and running from them...

613
00:55:40,160 --> 00:55:41,718
...but they are the gatekeepers.

614
00:55:41,960 --> 00:55:44,793
They're guarding all the doors
and holding all the keys.

615
00:55:45,040 --> 00:55:47,759
Sooner or later, someone will
have to fight them.

616
00:55:47,920 --> 00:55:49,069
Someone?

617
00:55:49,400 --> 00:55:50,753
I won't lie to you, Neo.

618
00:55:51,200 --> 00:55:55,830
Every single man or woman who
has fought an agent has died.

619
00:55:56,080 --> 00:55:58,355
But where they have failed,
you will succeed.

620
00:55:58,560 --> 00:55:59,549
Why?

621
00:55:59,800 --> 00:56:01,995
I've seen an agent punch
through a concrete wall.

622
00:56:02,240 --> 00:56:05,676
Men have emptied entire clips at them
and hit nothing but air.

623
00:56:05,920 --> 00:56:10,357
Yet their strength and speed are still
based in a world built on rules.

624
00:56:10,600 --> 00:56:11,669
Because of that...

625
00:56:11,920 --> 00:56:15,151
...they will never be as strong
or as fast as you can be.

626
00:56:19,280 --> 00:56:21,077
What are you telling me?

627
00:56:21,760 --> 00:56:23,159
That I can dodge bullets?

628
00:56:25,080 --> 00:56:26,399
No, Neo.

629
00:56:26,880 --> 00:56:29,678
I'm trying to tell you
that when you're ready...

630
00:56:30,520 --> 00:56:31,839
...you won't have to.

631
00:56:35,960 --> 00:56:36,949
We got trouble.

632
00:56:55,080 --> 00:56:57,435
-Did Zion send the warning?
-No, another ship.

633
00:57:00,560 --> 00:57:01,788
Shit.

634
00:57:02,040 --> 00:57:04,793
-Squiddy's sweeping in quick.
-Squiddy?

635
00:57:05,000 --> 00:57:08,072
A sentinel. A killing machine
designed for one thing.

636
00:57:08,320 --> 00:57:09,469
Search and destroy.

637
00:57:10,760 --> 00:57:11,875
Set her down there.

638
00:57:32,800 --> 00:57:34,836
How are we doing, Tank?

639
00:57:42,080 --> 00:57:43,195
Power off-line.

640
00:57:43,680 --> 00:57:45,591
EMP armed...

641
00:57:45,760 --> 00:57:47,557
-...and ready.
-EMP?

642
00:57:47,840 --> 00:57:49,637
Electromagnetic pulse.

643
00:57:49,880 --> 00:57:52,633
Disables any electrical system
in the blast radius.

644
00:57:52,880 --> 00:57:54,996
It's the only weapon we have
against the machines.

645
00:58:00,560 --> 00:58:03,552
-Where are we?
-Their old service and waste systems.

646
00:58:04,840 --> 00:58:05,829
Sewers.

647
00:58:06,040 --> 00:58:08,634
There used to be cities
that spanned hundreds of miles.

648
00:58:09,120 --> 00:58:10,951
Now these sewers are
all that's left.

649
00:58:11,200 --> 00:58:12,474
Quiet.

650
00:58:54,560 --> 00:58:56,630
You scared the bejesus out of me.

651
00:58:57,680 --> 00:58:59,511
-Sorry.
-It's okay.

652
00:59:02,320 --> 00:59:04,880
-ls that...?
-The Matrix?

653
00:59:07,920 --> 00:59:10,957
-Do you always look at it encoded?
-Well, you have to.

654
00:59:11,200 --> 00:59:14,158
The image translators work
for the construct program.

655
00:59:14,400 --> 00:59:17,676
But there's way too much information
to decode the Matrix.

656
00:59:17,920 --> 00:59:20,753
You get used to it.
I don't even see the code.

657
00:59:21,000 --> 00:59:24,276
All I see is blonde, brunette, redhead.

658
00:59:25,400 --> 00:59:26,719
Do you...

659
00:59:27,000 --> 00:59:28,035
...want a drink?

660
00:59:28,280 --> 00:59:29,269
Sure.

661
00:59:32,680 --> 00:59:34,079
You know...

662
00:59:34,960 --> 00:59:36,439
...I know what you're thinking.

663
00:59:36,680 --> 00:59:38,716
Because right now I'm thinking
the same thing.

664
00:59:39,000 --> 00:59:42,197
Actually, I've been thinking it
ever since I got here.

665
00:59:44,040 --> 00:59:46,918
Why, oh, why didn't I take
the blue pill?

666
00:59:58,800 --> 01:00:00,631
Good shit, huh?

667
01:00:00,960 --> 01:00:02,109
Dozer makes it.

668
01:00:02,560 --> 01:00:03,675
It's good for two things:

669
01:00:03,920 --> 01:00:06,878
Degreasing engines and
killing brain cells.

670
01:00:07,840 --> 01:00:09,956
So can I ask you something?

671
01:00:12,840 --> 01:00:14,398
Did he tell you why he did it?

672
01:00:16,920 --> 01:00:18,672
Why you're here?

673
01:00:22,200 --> 01:00:23,872
Jesus!

674
01:00:25,040 --> 01:00:26,871
What a mind job.

675
01:00:28,240 --> 01:00:30,913
So you're here to save the world.

676
01:00:32,360 --> 01:00:34,351
What do you say
to something like that?

677
01:00:39,320 --> 01:00:40,639
A little piece of advice.

678
01:00:42,360 --> 01:00:43,713
You see an agent...

679
01:00:44,040 --> 01:00:46,235
...you do what we do:

680
01:00:46,560 --> 01:00:48,039
Run.

681
01:00:48,360 --> 01:00:50,032
You run your ass off.

682
01:00:57,000 --> 01:00:58,638
Thanks for the drink.

683
01:01:03,160 --> 01:01:04,275
Sweet dreams.

684
01:01:08,120 --> 01:01:11,396
Do we have a deal, Mr. Reagan?

685
01:01:12,040 --> 01:01:13,109
You know...

686
01:01:14,480 --> 01:01:16,835
...I know this steak doesn't exist.

687
01:01:17,800 --> 01:01:20,439
I know that when I put it
in my mouth...

688
01:01:20,680 --> 01:01:23,638
...the Matrix is telling my brain
that it is...

689
01:01:23,920 --> 01:01:24,989
...juicy...

690
01:01:25,280 --> 01:01:26,918
...and delicious.

691
01:01:29,720 --> 01:01:30,914
After nine years...

692
01:01:31,920 --> 01:01:33,399
...you know what I realize?

693
01:01:40,920 --> 01:01:42,069
Ignorance is bliss.

694
01:01:46,920 --> 01:01:48,672
Then we have a deal.

695
01:01:51,080 --> 01:01:52,911
I don't want to remember nothing.

696
01:01:53,160 --> 01:01:55,594
Nothing. You understand?

697
01:01:59,480 --> 01:02:01,198
And I want to be rich.

698
01:02:02,480 --> 01:02:05,074
You know, someone important.

699
01:02:06,520 --> 01:02:07,589
Like an actor.

700
01:02:08,760 --> 01:02:11,752
Whatever you want, Mr. Reagan.

701
01:02:13,840 --> 01:02:15,319
Okay.

702
01:02:15,680 --> 01:02:17,989
You get my body
back in a power plant...

703
01:02:18,360 --> 01:02:20,032
...reinsert me into the Matrix...

704
01:02:20,360 --> 01:02:21,713
...I'll get you what you want.

705
01:02:21,960 --> 01:02:23,871
Access codes to the Zion mainframe.

706
01:02:24,120 --> 01:02:26,190
No. I told you, I don't know them.

707
01:02:29,040 --> 01:02:30,951
I can get you the man who does.

708
01:02:31,680 --> 01:02:33,398
Morpheus.

709
01:02:43,080 --> 01:02:46,390
Here you go, buddy.
Breakfast of champions.

710
01:02:47,680 --> 01:02:50,353
Close your eyes, it feels
like you're eating runny eggs.

711
01:02:50,600 --> 01:02:52,511
Or a bowl of snot.

712
01:02:52,720 --> 01:02:54,233
You know what it reminds me of?

713
01:02:56,000 --> 01:02:58,230
Tastee Wheat. Did you
ever eat T astee Wheat?

714
01:02:58,840 --> 01:03:00,478
No, but technically,
neither did you.

715
01:03:00,720 --> 01:03:02,676
That's exactly my point. Exactly.

716
01:03:02,920 --> 01:03:04,239
Because you have to wonder...

717
01:03:04,480 --> 01:03:07,597
... how do the machines really know
what T astee Wheat tasted like?

718
01:03:07,840 --> 01:03:09,193
Maybe they got it wrong.

719
01:03:09,440 --> 01:03:12,512
Maybe what I think T astee Wheat
tasted like actually tasted like...

720
01:03:12,800 --> 01:03:14,711
...oatmeal or tuna fish.

721
01:03:15,080 --> 01:03:17,799
That makes you wonder.
T ake chicken, for example.

722
01:03:18,040 --> 01:03:19,951
Maybe they didn't know
what to make it taste like...

723
01:03:20,200 --> 01:03:22,156
...which is why it tastes
like everything.

724
01:03:22,400 --> 01:03:24,118
-And maybe they--
-Shut up.

725
01:03:25,680 --> 01:03:27,079
It's a single-celled protein...

726
01:03:27,320 --> 01:03:30,232
...combined with synthetic aminos,
vitamins and minerals.

727
01:03:30,480 --> 01:03:31,674
Everything the body needs.

728
01:03:31,920 --> 01:03:34,673
It doesn't have everything
the body needs.

729
01:03:37,320 --> 01:03:40,278
I understand you've run through
the agent training program.

730
01:03:41,280 --> 01:03:43,236
You know, I wrote that program.

731
01:03:43,520 --> 01:03:44,748
Here it comes.

732
01:03:45,000 --> 01:03:46,877
-What did you think of her?
-Of who?

733
01:03:47,240 --> 01:03:50,152
The woman in the red dress.
I designed her.

734
01:03:50,480 --> 01:03:53,119
She doesn't talk very much...

735
01:03:53,360 --> 01:03:57,148
...but if you'd like to meet her,
I can arrange a more personal milieu.

736
01:03:57,400 --> 01:03:58,719
The digital pimp hard at work.

737
01:03:58,960 --> 01:04:01,110
Pay no attention to
these hypocrites, Neo.

738
01:04:02,360 --> 01:04:04,112
T o deny our own impulses...

739
01:04:04,360 --> 01:04:07,352
...is to deny the very thing
that makes us human.

740
01:04:09,200 --> 01:04:10,519
Dozer, when you're done...

741
01:04:10,760 --> 01:04:12,113
...bring the ship up to broadcast depth.

742
01:04:12,800 --> 01:04:14,074
We're going in.

743
01:04:14,760 --> 01:04:16,113
I'm taking Neo to see her.

744
01:04:20,080 --> 01:04:21,069
See who?

745
01:04:22,040 --> 01:04:23,234
The Oracle.

746
01:04:28,520 --> 01:04:29,999
Everyone, please observe...

747
01:04:30,320 --> 01:04:32,914
...the "fasten seat belt"
and "no smoking" signs are on.

748
01:04:33,400 --> 01:04:36,631
Sit back and enjoy your flight.

749
01:04:59,960 --> 01:05:00,949
We're in.

750
01:05:16,040 --> 01:05:17,109
We'll be back in an hour.

751
01:05:31,320 --> 01:05:32,673
Unbelievable...

752
01:05:33,480 --> 01:05:34,754
...isn't it?

753
01:05:38,200 --> 01:05:39,952
-God!
-What?

754
01:05:40,600 --> 01:05:41,919
I used to eat there.

755
01:05:44,080 --> 01:05:45,638
Really good noodles.

756
01:05:50,240 --> 01:05:52,629
I have these memories from my life.

757
01:05:55,000 --> 01:05:56,592
None of them happened.

758
01:05:57,200 --> 01:05:58,474
What does that mean?

759
01:05:58,720 --> 01:06:00,836
That the Matrix cannot tell you
who you are.

760
01:06:01,720 --> 01:06:02,869
But an oracle can?

761
01:06:03,320 --> 01:06:04,469
That's different.

762
01:06:09,040 --> 01:06:11,110
Did you go to her?

763
01:06:11,680 --> 01:06:12,795
Yes.

764
01:06:13,280 --> 01:06:14,599
What did she tell you?

765
01:06:17,720 --> 01:06:19,153
She told me....

766
01:06:20,160 --> 01:06:21,275
What?

767
01:06:24,920 --> 01:06:26,194
We're here.

768
01:06:27,400 --> 01:06:28,753
Come with me.

769
01:06:47,920 --> 01:06:50,309
So is this the same oracle
that made...

770
01:06:50,480 --> 01:06:51,595
...the prophecy?

771
01:06:51,840 --> 01:06:55,992
Yes. She's very old. She's been
with us since the beginning.

772
01:06:56,440 --> 01:06:58,351
-The beginning?
-Of the Resistance.

773
01:07:00,520 --> 01:07:02,795
And she knows what? Everything?

774
01:07:04,760 --> 01:07:06,591
She would say she knows enough.

775
01:07:07,680 --> 01:07:09,398
And she's never wrong.

776
01:07:11,520 --> 01:07:14,557
Try not to think of it
in terms of right and wrong.

777
01:07:14,880 --> 01:07:16,393
She is a guide, Neo.

778
01:07:16,760 --> 01:07:18,557
She can help you to find the path.

779
01:07:19,120 --> 01:07:20,235
She helped you?

780
01:07:22,640 --> 01:07:23,914
What did she tell you?

781
01:07:26,280 --> 01:07:28,396
That I would find the One.

782
01:07:41,000 --> 01:07:43,036
I told you I can only
show you the door.

783
01:07:43,720 --> 01:07:45,711
You have to walk through it.

784
01:07:49,360 --> 01:07:50,395
Hello, Neo.

785
01:07:50,640 --> 01:07:52,232
You're right on time.

786
01:07:59,840 --> 01:08:03,469
Make yourself at home, Morpheus.
Neo, come with me.

787
01:08:08,920 --> 01:08:10,433
These are the other Potentials.

788
01:08:10,680 --> 01:08:12,159
You can wait here.

789
01:08:51,320 --> 01:08:53,754
Do not try and bend the spoon.

790
01:08:54,120 --> 01:08:56,156
That's impossible.

791
01:08:56,960 --> 01:09:00,794
Instead, only try
to realize the truth.

792
01:09:01,320 --> 01:09:02,639
What truth?

793
01:09:02,880 --> 01:09:04,472
There is no spoon.

794
01:09:06,960 --> 01:09:08,234
There is no spoon?

795
01:09:08,480 --> 01:09:12,792
Then you'll see that it is not the spoon
that bends. It is only yourself.

796
01:09:28,160 --> 01:09:29,593
The Oracle will you see now.

797
01:09:39,840 --> 01:09:41,319
I know you're Neo.

798
01:09:41,920 --> 01:09:43,035
Be right with you.

799
01:09:44,040 --> 01:09:46,315
-You're the Oracle?
-Bingo.

800
01:09:48,920 --> 01:09:51,673
Not quite what you
were expecting, right?

801
01:09:52,680 --> 01:09:54,750
Almost done.

802
01:09:57,160 --> 01:09:58,718
Smell good, don't they?

803
01:10:01,360 --> 01:10:03,112
I'd ask you to sit down...

804
01:10:03,360 --> 01:10:05,635
...but you're not going to anyway.

805
01:10:06,120 --> 01:10:08,873
-And don't worry about the vase.
-What vase?

806
01:10:11,880 --> 01:10:12,995
That vase.

807
01:10:13,920 --> 01:10:14,909
I'm sorry.

808
01:10:15,160 --> 01:10:16,957
I said, don't worry about it.

809
01:10:18,080 --> 01:10:19,957
I'll get one of my kids to fix it.

810
01:10:20,560 --> 01:10:21,709
How did you know?

811
01:10:23,680 --> 01:10:27,309
What's really going to bake
your noodle later on is...

812
01:10:27,640 --> 01:10:30,473
...would you still have broken it
if I hadn't said anything?

813
01:10:35,080 --> 01:10:36,911
You're cuter than I thought.

814
01:10:39,840 --> 01:10:41,990
I can see why she likes you.

815
01:10:42,840 --> 01:10:43,875
Who?

816
01:10:44,120 --> 01:10:45,872
Not too bright, though.

817
01:10:49,040 --> 01:10:51,998
You know why Morpheus
brought you to see me.

818
01:10:54,040 --> 01:10:55,155
So...

819
01:10:56,080 --> 01:10:57,399
...what do you think?

820
01:10:59,160 --> 01:11:00,832
Do you think you are the One?

821
01:11:02,720 --> 01:11:03,709
I don't know.

822
01:11:07,000 --> 01:11:08,353
You know what that means?

823
01:11:09,160 --> 01:11:10,275
It's Latin.

824
01:11:10,640 --> 01:11:12,756
Means, "Know thyself. "

825
01:11:14,160 --> 01:11:16,037
I'll let you in on a little secret.

826
01:11:18,200 --> 01:11:21,875
Being the One is just
like being in love.

827
01:11:22,560 --> 01:11:25,313
No one can tell you you're in love.
You just know it...

828
01:11:25,560 --> 01:11:26,629
...through and through.

829
01:11:26,960 --> 01:11:28,916
Balls to bones.

830
01:11:31,360 --> 01:11:33,157
Well...

831
01:11:34,040 --> 01:11:36,031
...I'd better have a look at you.

832
01:11:37,320 --> 01:11:38,753
Open your mouth. Say, "Ah. "

833
01:11:52,560 --> 01:11:54,152
Okay....

834
01:11:54,760 --> 01:11:59,515
Now I'm supposed to say,
"Hmm, that's interesting, but.... "

835
01:12:00,000 --> 01:12:01,069
Then you say:

836
01:12:01,640 --> 01:12:02,868
But what?

837
01:12:03,120 --> 01:12:06,908
But you already know
what I'm going to tell you.

838
01:12:08,280 --> 01:12:11,113
-I'm not the One.
-Sorry, kid.

839
01:12:12,680 --> 01:12:14,591
You got the gift...

840
01:12:15,560 --> 01:12:17,676
...but it looks like
you're waiting for something.

841
01:12:22,360 --> 01:12:26,148
-What?
-Your next life, maybe. Who knows?

842
01:12:26,720 --> 01:12:28,870
That's the way these things go.

843
01:12:29,720 --> 01:12:32,188
-What's funny?
-Morpheus.

844
01:12:35,520 --> 01:12:37,158
He almost had me convinced.

845
01:12:37,400 --> 01:12:38,469
I know.

846
01:12:39,960 --> 01:12:41,996
Poor Morpheus.

847
01:12:44,280 --> 01:12:47,272
Without him, we're lost.

848
01:12:48,760 --> 01:12:50,830
What do you mean, "without him"?

849
01:12:54,680 --> 01:12:56,511
Are you sure you want
to hear this?

850
01:12:58,640 --> 01:13:01,279
Morpheus believes in you, Neo.

851
01:13:02,920 --> 01:13:04,990
And no one, not you, not even me...

852
01:13:05,240 --> 01:13:07,390
...can convince him otherwise.

853
01:13:07,760 --> 01:13:10,035
He believes it so blindly...

854
01:13:10,320 --> 01:13:14,472
...that he's going to sacrifice
his life to save yours.

855
01:13:14,720 --> 01:13:18,508
-What?
-You're going to have to make a choice.

856
01:13:19,120 --> 01:13:22,556
In the one hand,
you'll have Morpheus' life.

857
01:13:23,040 --> 01:13:25,793
And in the other hand,
you'll have your own.

858
01:13:27,160 --> 01:13:29,355
One of you is going to die.

859
01:13:31,360 --> 01:13:34,511
Which one will be up to you.

860
01:13:35,840 --> 01:13:37,671
I'm sorry, kiddo. I really am.

861
01:13:37,920 --> 01:13:39,512
You have a good soul.

862
01:13:40,560 --> 01:13:43,154
And I hate giving
good people bad news.

863
01:13:46,160 --> 01:13:47,559
Don't worry about it.

864
01:13:47,800 --> 01:13:50,109
As soon as you
step outside that door...

865
01:13:50,360 --> 01:13:52,396
...you'll start feeling better.

866
01:13:53,080 --> 01:13:56,709
You'll remember you don't believe
in any of this fate crap.

867
01:13:57,520 --> 01:14:00,159
You're in control of your own life.

868
01:14:00,960 --> 01:14:02,188
Remember?

869
01:14:04,000 --> 01:14:05,592
Here...

870
01:14:06,760 --> 01:14:08,239
...take a cookie.

871
01:14:08,760 --> 01:14:11,957
I promise, by the time
you're done eating it...

872
01:14:12,880 --> 01:14:15,155
...you'll feel right as rain.

873
01:14:24,000 --> 01:14:25,274
What was said...

874
01:14:25,880 --> 01:14:27,279
...was for you...

875
01:14:27,800 --> 01:14:29,552
...and for you alone.

876
01:14:51,560 --> 01:14:52,629
They're on the way.

877
01:15:21,200 --> 01:15:22,189
What is that?

878
01:15:36,360 --> 01:15:37,713
Oh, déjà vu.

879
01:15:41,080 --> 01:15:42,115
What did you just say?

880
01:15:42,360 --> 01:15:43,793
Nothing.
Just déjà vu.

881
01:15:44,040 --> 01:15:45,598
-What did you see?
-What happened?

882
01:15:46,960 --> 01:15:49,030
A black cat went past us...

883
01:15:49,280 --> 01:15:50,838
...then another just like it.

884
01:15:51,080 --> 01:15:52,559
Was it the same cat?

885
01:15:53,480 --> 01:15:54,629
I'm not sure.

886
01:15:55,400 --> 01:15:57,118
Switch, Apoc.

887
01:16:00,280 --> 01:16:01,269
What is it?

888
01:16:01,520 --> 01:16:05,752
A déjà vu is usually a glitch in the
Matrix when they change something.

889
01:16:08,800 --> 01:16:09,789
Oh, my God.

890
01:16:11,560 --> 01:16:13,551
Let's go.

891
01:16:17,520 --> 01:16:19,192
They cut the hard line.
It's a trap! Get out!

892
01:16:24,520 --> 01:16:25,669
Oh, no.

893
01:16:27,080 --> 01:16:28,069
Oh, no.

894
01:17:04,320 --> 01:17:06,675
That's what they changed.
We're trapped.

895
01:17:06,920 --> 01:17:08,717
Be calm. Give me your phone.

896
01:17:08,960 --> 01:17:10,439
They'll be able to track it.

897
01:17:10,680 --> 01:17:12,033
We have no choice.

898
01:17:13,400 --> 01:17:14,549
Operator.

899
01:17:14,880 --> 01:17:17,599
Find a structural drawing of
this building. Find it fast.

900
01:17:25,120 --> 01:17:27,588
-Got it!
-I need the main wet-wall.

901
01:17:30,480 --> 01:17:31,515
Eighth floor.

902
01:17:31,720 --> 01:17:33,233
They're on the eighth floor.

903
01:17:33,520 --> 01:17:34,919
Switch, straight ahead.

904
01:17:42,640 --> 01:17:44,710
I hope the Oracle
gave you some good news.

905
01:17:52,640 --> 01:17:54,073
Now left. That's it.

906
01:17:54,360 --> 01:17:55,349
Good.

907
01:18:04,680 --> 01:18:05,908
Where are they?

908
01:19:03,880 --> 01:19:04,995
They' re in the walls.

909
01:19:06,400 --> 01:19:07,515
In the walls!

910
01:19:28,040 --> 01:19:29,678
It's an agent!

911
01:19:38,240 --> 01:19:41,277
You must get Neo out!
He's all that matters!

912
01:19:41,560 --> 01:19:42,709
No, Morpheus! Don't!

913
01:19:42,960 --> 01:19:44,439
Trinity, go!

914
01:19:44,600 --> 01:19:45,919
Go!

915
01:19:51,880 --> 01:19:53,711
-We can't leave him!
-We have to!

916
01:20:17,960 --> 01:20:19,871
Come on!

917
01:20:23,480 --> 01:20:27,155
The great Morpheus.
We meet at last.

918
01:20:27,680 --> 01:20:28,749
And you are?

919
01:20:29,000 --> 01:20:30,672
A Smith.

920
01:20:30,920 --> 01:20:32,148
Agent Smith.

921
01:20:32,720 --> 01:20:34,676
You all look the same to me.

922
01:21:28,040 --> 01:21:29,268
Take him.

923
01:21:41,960 --> 01:21:43,712
-Operator.
-I need an exit, fast.

924
01:21:45,720 --> 01:21:48,518
There was an accident.
Goddamn car accident.

925
01:21:48,840 --> 01:21:50,558
All of a sudden, boom.

926
01:21:50,800 --> 01:21:52,119
Somebody up there still likes me.

927
01:21:52,360 --> 01:21:53,554
I got you.

928
01:21:54,040 --> 01:21:55,871
Just get me out of here fast.

929
01:21:56,120 --> 01:21:58,680
Nearest exit, Franklin and Erie.
An old TV repair shop.

930
01:21:58,920 --> 01:21:59,909
Right.

931
01:22:02,920 --> 01:22:04,433
-Operator.
- Tank, it's me.

932
01:22:04,680 --> 01:22:05,795
Is Morpheus alive?

933
01:22:06,160 --> 01:22:07,388
Is Morpheus alive, T ank?

934
01:22:07,800 --> 01:22:09,631
Yes. They're moving him.
I don 't know where.

935
01:22:09,840 --> 01:22:13,150
-He's alive. We need an exit.
-You' re not far from Cypher.

936
01:22:13,400 --> 01:22:14,674
-Cypher?
-I know.

937
01:22:14,920 --> 01:22:16,911
-I sent him to Franklin and Erie.
-Got it.

938
01:22:25,640 --> 01:22:26,789
Got him.

939
01:22:37,280 --> 01:22:38,269
Where are they?

940
01:22:38,520 --> 01:22:39,714
Making the call.

941
01:22:40,360 --> 01:22:41,475
Good.

942
01:22:54,480 --> 01:22:56,198
You first.

943
01:22:58,320 --> 01:22:59,514
Shit!

944
01:23:07,840 --> 01:23:09,910
I don't know. It just went dead.

945
01:23:35,640 --> 01:23:36,789
Hello, Trinity.

946
01:23:37,200 --> 01:23:38,474
Cypher? Where's T ank?

947
01:23:43,840 --> 01:23:44,829
You know...

948
01:23:46,480 --> 01:23:48,516
...for a long time...

949
01:23:49,680 --> 01:23:52,478
... I thought I was in love with you.

950
01:23:53,200 --> 01:23:55,156
I used to dream about you.

951
01:23:56,200 --> 01:23:58,794
You' re a beautiful woman, T rinity.

952
01:23:59,040 --> 01:24:01,315
Too bad things had to
turn out this way.

953
01:24:01,800 --> 01:24:02,835
You killed them.

954
01:24:03,320 --> 01:24:04,753
-What?
-Oh, God.

955
01:24:05,000 --> 01:24:06,353
I' m tired, T rinity.

956
01:24:07,720 --> 01:24:09,517
I' m tired of this war...

957
01:24:09,800 --> 01:24:12,519
...tired of fighting.
I' m tired of this ship...

958
01:24:12,840 --> 01:24:17,277
...of being cold, of eating
the same goddamn goop every day.

959
01:24:19,480 --> 01:24:20,469
But most of all...

960
01:24:21,040 --> 01:24:24,271
...I'm tired of that jackoff
and all of his bullshit.

961
01:24:25,360 --> 01:24:26,588
Surprise, asshole!

962
01:24:27,120 --> 01:24:29,236
I bet you never saw this coming...

963
01:24:29,480 --> 01:24:30,469
...did you?

964
01:24:32,680 --> 01:24:34,955
God, I wish I could be there...

965
01:24:35,520 --> 01:24:36,953
...when they break you.

966
01:24:37,960 --> 01:24:40,997
I wish I could walk in
just when it happens...

967
01:24:41,680 --> 01:24:43,318
...so right then...

968
01:24:43,560 --> 01:24:44,834
...you'd know it was me.

969
01:24:45,240 --> 01:24:48,073
-You gave them Morpheus.
-He lied to us, Trinity.

970
01:24:48,640 --> 01:24:50,073
He tricked us!

971
01:24:50,600 --> 01:24:52,511
If you had told us the truth...

972
01:24:52,760 --> 01:24:55,513
...we would've told you to shove
that red pill up your ass!

973
01:24:55,760 --> 01:24:58,911
-That is not true, Cypher. He set us free.
- "Free. "

974
01:24:59,160 --> 01:25:00,798
You call this free?

975
01:25:03,120 --> 01:25:05,509
All I do is what he tells me to do.

976
01:25:07,040 --> 01:25:09,838
If I had to choose between
that and the Matrix...

977
01:25:10,960 --> 01:25:12,109
... I choose the Matrix.

978
01:25:12,360 --> 01:25:13,952
The Matrix isn't real.

979
01:25:14,200 --> 01:25:15,553
I disagree, Trinity.

980
01:25:15,800 --> 01:25:17,950
I think the Matrix...

981
01:25:18,280 --> 01:25:20,748
...can be more real than this world.

982
01:25:22,840 --> 01:25:25,229
All I do is pull the plug here.

983
01:25:25,480 --> 01:25:26,754
But there...

984
01:25:27,280 --> 01:25:29,475
... you have to watch Apoc die.

985
01:25:36,920 --> 01:25:38,558
Welcome to the real world.

986
01:25:38,720 --> 01:25:39,755
But you' re out.

987
01:25:40,000 --> 01:25:42,309
- You can 't go back.
-That's what you think.

988
01:25:42,560 --> 01:25:43,993
They'll reinsert my body.

989
01:25:44,240 --> 01:25:47,710
I go back to sleep. When I wake up,
I won 't remember a thing.

990
01:25:47,960 --> 01:25:49,029
By the way...

991
01:25:49,200 --> 01:25:51,998
...if you have anything important
to say to Switch...

992
01:25:52,480 --> 01:25:54,596
-...say it now.
-No, please don't.

993
01:25:55,120 --> 01:25:56,678
Not like this.

994
01:25:58,320 --> 01:25:59,878
Not like this.

995
01:26:04,160 --> 01:26:05,149
T oo late.

996
01:26:05,600 --> 01:26:07,113
Goddamn you, Cypher!

997
01:26:07,360 --> 01:26:09,157
Don't hate me, Trinity.

998
01:26:09,520 --> 01:26:11,317
I'm just a messenger.

999
01:26:11,720 --> 01:26:14,757
And right now,
I'm going to prove it to you.

1000
01:26:15,800 --> 01:26:17,392
If Morpheus was right...

1001
01:26:17,920 --> 01:26:19,717
...there's no way
I can pull this plug.

1002
01:26:20,280 --> 01:26:21,713
If Neo 's the One...

1003
01:26:22,200 --> 01:26:23,952
... then there'd have to be...

1004
01:26:24,200 --> 01:26:26,668
...some kind of a miracle to stop me.

1005
01:26:27,160 --> 01:26:28,434
Right?

1006
01:26:28,600 --> 01:26:31,797
I mean, how can he be the One
if he's dead?

1007
01:26:33,120 --> 01:26:35,270
You never did answer me before...

1008
01:26:35,560 --> 01:26:37,790
...if you bought into
Morpheus ' bullshit.

1009
01:26:38,160 --> 01:26:41,232
Come on. All I want
is a little yes or no.

1010
01:26:42,560 --> 01:26:44,790
Look into his eyes...

1011
01:26:45,520 --> 01:26:46,953
... those big, pretty eyes...

1012
01:26:49,600 --> 01:26:50,874
...and tell me...

1013
01:26:51,560 --> 01:26:52,788
... yes...

1014
01:26:53,080 --> 01:26:54,399
... or no.

1015
01:26:55,640 --> 01:26:56,709
Y es.

1016
01:26:57,320 --> 01:26:58,389
I don't believe it.

1017
01:26:59,760 --> 01:27:04,311
Believe it or not, you piece of shit,
you' re still going to burn!

1018
01:27:21,960 --> 01:27:23,154
You first.

1019
01:27:30,880 --> 01:27:31,869
You' re hurt.

1020
01:27:32,200 --> 01:27:33,235
I'll be all right.

1021
01:27:35,920 --> 01:27:37,035
Dozer?

1022
01:27:54,560 --> 01:27:56,835
Have you ever stood and stared at it?

1023
01:27:57,680 --> 01:28:00,672
Marveled at its beauty...

1024
01:28:01,040 --> 01:28:03,190
...its genius?

1025
01:28:04,320 --> 01:28:06,117
Billions of people...

1026
01:28:06,360 --> 01:28:08,999
...just living out their lives.

1027
01:28:10,000 --> 01:28:11,592
Oblivious.

1028
01:28:16,000 --> 01:28:18,753
Did you know that the first Matrix...

1029
01:28:19,000 --> 01:28:23,516
...was designed to be a perfect
human world where none suffered...

1030
01:28:23,960 --> 01:28:26,758
...where everyone would be happy.

1031
01:28:27,280 --> 01:28:28,713
It was a disaster.

1032
01:28:28,960 --> 01:28:33,112
No one would accept the program.
Entire crops were lost.

1033
01:28:33,960 --> 01:28:35,632
Some believe that...

1034
01:28:35,880 --> 01:28:40,078
...we lacked the programming language
to describe your perfect world.

1035
01:28:40,320 --> 01:28:43,073
But I believe that, as a species...

1036
01:28:43,320 --> 01:28:46,995
...human beings define
their reality through misery...

1037
01:28:47,240 --> 01:28:48,559
...and suffering.

1038
01:28:48,800 --> 01:28:51,394
So the perfect world was a dream...

1039
01:28:51,640 --> 01:28:56,270
...that your primitive cerebrum
kept trying to wake up from.

1040
01:28:57,560 --> 01:29:01,075
Which is why the Matrix was
redesigned to this.

1041
01:29:01,520 --> 01:29:02,953
The peak...

1042
01:29:03,200 --> 01:29:04,553
...of your civilization.

1043
01:29:04,800 --> 01:29:06,950
I say, "your civilization"...

1044
01:29:07,200 --> 01:29:11,159
...because when we started thinking
for you, it became our civilization...

1045
01:29:11,400 --> 01:29:14,358
...which is, of course,
what this is all about.

1046
01:29:15,640 --> 01:29:18,108
Evolution, Morpheus.

1047
01:29:18,400 --> 01:29:19,674
Evolution.

1048
01:29:21,880 --> 01:29:23,677
Like the dinosaur.

1049
01:29:25,760 --> 01:29:27,318
Look out that window.

1050
01:29:28,000 --> 01:29:30,036
You had your time.

1051
01:29:30,720 --> 01:29:34,474
The future is our world, Morpheus.

1052
01:29:34,800 --> 01:29:37,075
The future is our time.

1053
01:29:40,880 --> 01:29:41,915
There could be a problem.

1054
01:29:43,160 --> 01:29:46,391
-What are they doing to him?
-They're breaking into his mind.

1055
01:29:46,640 --> 01:29:48,710
It's like hacking a computer.
All it takes is time.

1056
01:29:48,960 --> 01:29:50,109
How much time?

1057
01:29:50,360 --> 01:29:53,352
Depends on the mind.
But eventually, it'll crack...

1058
01:29:53,600 --> 01:29:57,832
...and his alpha patterns
will change from this to this.

1059
01:29:58,080 --> 01:30:00,913
When it does, he'll tell them
anything they want to know.

1060
01:30:01,160 --> 01:30:02,149
What do they want?

1061
01:30:02,400 --> 01:30:06,279
The leader of every ship is given codes
to Zion's mainframe computer.

1062
01:30:06,520 --> 01:30:09,318
If an agent got the codes
and got into Zion's mainframe...

1063
01:30:09,560 --> 01:30:12,518
...they could destroy us.
We can't let that happen.

1064
01:30:13,320 --> 01:30:14,878
Zion's more important than me...

1065
01:30:15,040 --> 01:30:16,189
...or you...

1066
01:30:16,360 --> 01:30:17,509
...or even Morpheus.

1067
01:30:21,160 --> 01:30:22,752
There has to be
something we can do.

1068
01:30:23,160 --> 01:30:25,071
There is. We pull the plug.

1069
01:30:28,040 --> 01:30:29,712
You're going to kill him?

1070
01:30:29,960 --> 01:30:31,075
Kill Morpheus?

1071
01:30:31,680 --> 01:30:33,238
We don't have a choice.

1072
01:30:39,760 --> 01:30:42,558
Never send a human
to do a machine's job.

1073
01:30:42,800 --> 01:30:44,472
If the insider has failed...

1074
01:30:44,720 --> 01:30:47,792
...they'll sever the connection
as soon as possible, unless--

1075
01:30:48,040 --> 01:30:49,678
They're dead. In either case--

1076
01:30:49,920 --> 01:30:53,310
We have no choice. Continue as planned.
Deploy the sentinels.

1077
01:30:53,560 --> 01:30:54,595
Immediately.

1078
01:30:59,640 --> 01:31:02,200
Morpheus, you were more
than a leader to us.

1079
01:31:03,120 --> 01:31:05,236
You were a father.

1080
01:31:06,720 --> 01:31:08,597
We'll miss you always.

1081
01:31:15,080 --> 01:31:16,354
Stop!

1082
01:31:17,520 --> 01:31:18,669
I don't believe this is happening.

1083
01:31:18,920 --> 01:31:20,876
-Neo, this has to be done.
-Does it?

1084
01:31:21,640 --> 01:31:22,959
I don't know.

1085
01:31:23,280 --> 01:31:24,759
This can't be just coincidence.

1086
01:31:24,960 --> 01:31:27,030
-What are you talking about?
-The Oracle.

1087
01:31:27,280 --> 01:31:28,998
She told me this would happen.

1088
01:31:29,400 --> 01:31:33,393
She told me that I would
have to make a choice.

1089
01:31:33,840 --> 01:31:35,034
What choice?

1090
01:31:37,880 --> 01:31:40,269
-What are you doing?
-I'm going in.

1091
01:31:40,600 --> 01:31:42,830
-No, you're not.
-I have to.

1092
01:31:43,040 --> 01:31:46,510
Neo, Morpheus sacrificed himself
so that we could get you out.

1093
01:31:46,760 --> 01:31:48,591
There is no way
that you're going back in.

1094
01:31:49,160 --> 01:31:52,277
Morpheus did what he did because
he believed I'm something I'm not.

1095
01:31:53,840 --> 01:31:56,957
-What?
-I'm not the One, Trinity.

1096
01:31:57,320 --> 01:32:00,153
-The Oracle hit me with that too.
-No, you have to be.

1097
01:32:00,400 --> 01:32:02,960
I'm sorry, I'm not.
I'm just another guy.

1098
01:32:03,600 --> 01:32:04,794
No, Neo, that's not true.

1099
01:32:05,360 --> 01:32:06,634
It can't be true.

1100
01:32:06,960 --> 01:32:08,996
Why?

1101
01:32:12,120 --> 01:32:15,317
This is loco. They've got Morpheus
in a military-controlled building.

1102
01:32:15,560 --> 01:32:19,758
Even if you somehow got inside, those
are agents holding him. Three of them.

1103
01:32:21,000 --> 01:32:24,754
I want Morpheus back too, but
what you're talking about is suicide.

1104
01:32:25,000 --> 01:32:27,673
That's what it looks like,
but it's not.

1105
01:32:27,920 --> 01:32:30,195
I can't explain to you why it's not.

1106
01:32:31,240 --> 01:32:34,789
Morpheus believed something, and
he was ready to give his life for it.

1107
01:32:35,040 --> 01:32:37,918
I understand that now.
That's why I have to go.

1108
01:32:38,160 --> 01:32:40,594
-Why?
-Because I believe in something.

1109
01:32:40,800 --> 01:32:42,472
What?

1110
01:32:43,000 --> 01:32:44,638
I believe I can bring him back.

1111
01:33:00,920 --> 01:33:02,751
-What are you doing?
-Going with you.

1112
01:33:03,040 --> 01:33:05,918
-No, you're not.
-"No"?

1113
01:33:06,080 --> 01:33:08,116
Let me tell you what I believe.

1114
01:33:08,600 --> 01:33:10,875
Morpheus means more to me
than he does to you.

1115
01:33:11,200 --> 01:33:15,318
I believe if you are serious about
saving him, you will need my help.

1116
01:33:15,560 --> 01:33:17,516
And since I am the ranking officer...

1117
01:33:17,760 --> 01:33:20,513
...if you don't like it,
I believe you can go to hell.

1118
01:33:21,240 --> 01:33:23,549
Because you aren't going anywhere else.

1119
01:33:23,960 --> 01:33:25,439
Tank...

1120
01:33:25,600 --> 01:33:26,715
...Ioad us up.

1121
01:33:35,920 --> 01:33:39,071
I'd like to share
a revelation that I've had...

1122
01:33:39,480 --> 01:33:40,959
...during my time here.

1123
01:33:41,200 --> 01:33:45,034
It came to me when I tried
to classify your species...

1124
01:33:45,280 --> 01:33:47,430
...and I realized...

1125
01:33:47,680 --> 01:33:49,875
...that you're not actually mammals.

1126
01:33:52,000 --> 01:33:54,355
Every mammal on this planet...

1127
01:33:54,680 --> 01:33:59,390
...instinctively develops an equilibrium
with the surrounding environment.

1128
01:33:59,640 --> 01:34:01,392
But you humans do not.

1129
01:34:01,920 --> 01:34:05,310
You move to an area
and you multiply...

1130
01:34:05,560 --> 01:34:09,872
...and multiply until every
natural resource is consumed.

1131
01:34:10,200 --> 01:34:12,191
The only way you can survive...

1132
01:34:12,480 --> 01:34:15,313
...is to spread to another area.

1133
01:34:20,520 --> 01:34:23,273
There is another organism
on this planet...

1134
01:34:23,520 --> 01:34:25,397
...that follows the same pattern.

1135
01:34:26,000 --> 01:34:27,592
Do you know what it is?

1136
01:34:27,960 --> 01:34:29,712
A virus.

1137
01:34:31,000 --> 01:34:33,912
Human beings are a disease.

1138
01:34:34,280 --> 01:34:35,759
A cancer of this planet.

1139
01:34:36,000 --> 01:34:38,036
You are a plague.

1140
01:34:38,560 --> 01:34:41,393
And we are the cure.

1141
01:34:42,360 --> 01:34:43,713
Okay, so what do you need?

1142
01:34:44,320 --> 01:34:45,389
Besides a miracle.

1143
01:34:45,960 --> 01:34:47,109
Guns.

1144
01:34:47,800 --> 01:34:49,074
Lots of guns.

1145
01:35:01,400 --> 01:35:03,834
No one has ever done
anything like this.

1146
01:35:05,000 --> 01:35:06,831
That's why it's going to work.

1147
01:35:10,760 --> 01:35:12,637
Why isn't the serum working?

1148
01:35:13,200 --> 01:35:15,395
Perhaps we're asking
the wrong questions.

1149
01:35:17,400 --> 01:35:18,594
Leave me with him.

1150
01:35:21,080 --> 01:35:22,149
Now.

1151
01:35:32,920 --> 01:35:34,433
Hold on, Morpheus.

1152
01:35:34,680 --> 01:35:37,274
They're coming for you.
They're coming.

1153
01:35:39,560 --> 01:35:41,596
Can you hear me, Morpheus?

1154
01:35:41,840 --> 01:35:44,400
I'm going to be honest...

1155
01:35:44,760 --> 01:35:45,909
...with you.

1156
01:35:50,120 --> 01:35:51,473
I...

1157
01:35:52,200 --> 01:35:53,394
...hate...

1158
01:35:53,640 --> 01:35:55,517
...this place...

1159
01:35:55,840 --> 01:35:58,035
...this zoo...

1160
01:35:58,280 --> 01:35:59,349
...this prison...

1161
01:35:59,600 --> 01:36:02,637
...this reality,
whatever you want to call it.

1162
01:36:02,880 --> 01:36:05,075
I can't stand it any longer.

1163
01:36:05,800 --> 01:36:07,597
It's the smell.

1164
01:36:08,920 --> 01:36:10,717
If there is such a thing.

1165
01:36:11,040 --> 01:36:14,191
I feel saturated by it.

1166
01:36:15,640 --> 01:36:17,949
I can taste...

1167
01:36:18,760 --> 01:36:20,716
...your stink.

1168
01:36:20,960 --> 01:36:24,555
And every time I do, I fear that
I have somehow been infected by it.

1169
01:36:24,800 --> 01:36:26,358
It's repulsive.

1170
01:36:26,520 --> 01:36:27,839
Isn't it?

1171
01:36:29,920 --> 01:36:32,115
I must get out of here.

1172
01:36:32,520 --> 01:36:34,636
I must get free.

1173
01:36:34,880 --> 01:36:37,633
And in this mind is the key.

1174
01:36:37,880 --> 01:36:39,472
My key.

1175
01:36:39,720 --> 01:36:42,473
Once Zion is destroyed,
there is no need for me to be here.

1176
01:36:42,720 --> 01:36:44,278
Do you understand?

1177
01:36:44,560 --> 01:36:45,879
I need the codes.

1178
01:36:46,120 --> 01:36:48,350
I have to get inside Zion...

1179
01:36:48,680 --> 01:36:51,069
...and you have to tell me how.

1180
01:36:51,480 --> 01:36:53,277
You're going to tell me...

1181
01:36:53,520 --> 01:36:55,590
...or you're going to die.

1182
01:37:14,960 --> 01:37:18,839
Please remove any metallic items
you're carrying. Keys, loose change.

1183
01:37:21,720 --> 01:37:22,709
Holy shit!

1184
01:37:34,320 --> 01:37:36,914
Backup. Send backup.

1185
01:37:59,720 --> 01:38:00,835
Freeze!

1186
01:40:10,360 --> 01:40:12,396
What were you doing?

1187
01:40:13,080 --> 01:40:14,308
He doesn't know.

1188
01:40:14,560 --> 01:40:15,993
Know what?

1189
01:40:42,920 --> 01:40:45,309
I think they're trying to save him.

1190
01:40:59,560 --> 01:41:01,232
There is no spoon.

1191
01:41:29,640 --> 01:41:31,710
Find them and destroy them!

1192
01:41:33,280 --> 01:41:35,077
I repeat. We're under attack!

1193
01:42:07,480 --> 01:42:08,469
Help!

1194
01:42:29,600 --> 01:42:30,749
Only human.

1195
01:42:31,800 --> 01:42:33,597
Dodge this.

1196
01:42:45,400 --> 01:42:46,879
-How did you do that?
-Do what?

1197
01:42:47,240 --> 01:42:50,994
You moved like they do.
I've never seen anyone move that fast.

1198
01:42:52,080 --> 01:42:53,399
It wasn't fast enough.

1199
01:42:56,040 --> 01:42:57,268
Can you fly that thing?

1200
01:42:58,560 --> 01:43:00,278
Not yet.

1201
01:43:02,400 --> 01:43:03,469
Operator.

1202
01:43:03,680 --> 01:43:06,717
I need a pilot program
for a B-212 helicopter.

1203
01:43:07,160 --> 01:43:08,388
Hurry.

1204
01:43:16,000 --> 01:43:17,558
Let's go.

1205
01:43:32,040 --> 01:43:33,075
No.

1206
01:44:22,560 --> 01:44:25,074
Morpheus, get up.
Get up, get up.

1207
01:45:01,560 --> 01:45:03,232
He's not going to make it.

1208
01:45:11,960 --> 01:45:12,949
Got you.

1209
01:46:57,400 --> 01:46:58,753
I knew it.

1210
01:46:59,240 --> 01:47:00,514
He's the One.

1211
01:47:15,840 --> 01:47:17,956
Do you believe it now, Trinity?

1212
01:47:23,640 --> 01:47:25,517
The Oracle.

1213
01:47:25,680 --> 01:47:27,955
-She told me--
-She told you...

1214
01:47:28,320 --> 01:47:29,833
...what you needed to hear.

1215
01:47:30,120 --> 01:47:31,394
That's all.

1216
01:47:32,400 --> 01:47:35,233
Sooner or later you'll realize,
just as I did...

1217
01:47:35,560 --> 01:47:37,755
...there's a difference
between knowing the path...

1218
01:47:38,480 --> 01:47:39,708
...and walking the path.

1219
01:47:42,640 --> 01:47:43,789
Operator.

1220
01:47:44,680 --> 01:47:47,114
-It's good to hear your voice.
-We need an exit.

1221
01:47:47,360 --> 01:47:50,033
Got one ready. Subway station,
State and Balboa.

1222
01:48:01,960 --> 01:48:03,473
Damn it!

1223
01:48:03,720 --> 01:48:04,869
The trace was completed.

1224
01:48:05,120 --> 01:48:08,556
-We have their position.
-Sentinels are standing by.

1225
01:48:10,200 --> 01:48:11,633
Order the strike.

1226
01:48:17,920 --> 01:48:19,876
They're not out yet.

1227
01:48:30,560 --> 01:48:31,834
You first, Morpheus.

1228
01:48:51,680 --> 01:48:53,875
Neo, I want to tell you something...

1229
01:48:57,000 --> 01:49:00,788
...but I'm afraid of
what it could mean if I do.

1230
01:49:04,240 --> 01:49:07,391
Everything the Oracle
told me has come true.

1231
01:49:10,040 --> 01:49:11,519
Everything but this.

1232
01:49:12,880 --> 01:49:13,949
But what?

1233
01:49:39,200 --> 01:49:40,758
-What happened?
-An agent.

1234
01:49:41,000 --> 01:49:42,877
-Send me back.
-I can't.

1235
01:49:44,800 --> 01:49:46,711
Mr. Anderson.

1236
01:49:48,800 --> 01:49:50,119
Run, Neo. Run.

1237
01:49:55,200 --> 01:49:56,758
What is he doing?

1238
01:49:57,000 --> 01:49:58,194
He's beginning to believe.

1239
01:50:24,080 --> 01:50:25,399
You're empty.

1240
01:50:25,960 --> 01:50:27,188
So are you.

1241
01:50:59,000 --> 01:51:01,878
I'm going to enjoy watching you die...

1242
01:51:02,960 --> 01:51:03,949
...Mr. Anderson.

1243
01:51:43,240 --> 01:51:45,231
Jesus, he's killing him.

1244
01:53:07,880 --> 01:53:09,916
You hear that, Mr. Anderson?

1245
01:53:10,640 --> 01:53:13,518
That is the sound of inevitability.

1246
01:53:16,000 --> 01:53:19,197
It is the sound of your death.

1247
01:53:20,080 --> 01:53:22,310
Goodbye, Mr. Anderson.

1248
01:53:22,560 --> 01:53:24,118
My name...

1249
01:53:27,000 --> 01:53:28,956
...is Neo.

1250
01:53:59,880 --> 01:54:01,916
-What happened?
-I don't know. I lost him.

1251
01:54:04,400 --> 01:54:05,389
Oh, shit.

1252
01:54:17,280 --> 01:54:18,679
Sentinels.

1253
01:54:19,400 --> 01:54:21,550
-How long?
-Five, maybe six minutes.

1254
01:54:23,520 --> 01:54:25,590
Tank, charge the EMP.

1255
01:54:25,840 --> 01:54:28,752
-We can't use that until he's out.
-I know. Don't worry.

1256
01:54:29,800 --> 01:54:30,915
He's gonna make it.

1257
01:54:31,160 --> 01:54:32,957
Flat or pumps? No, just--

1258
01:54:33,200 --> 01:54:35,953
What the shit? That's my phone!

1259
01:54:36,360 --> 01:54:37,873
That guy took my phone!

1260
01:54:40,160 --> 01:54:43,391
-Got him! He's on the run.
-Mr. Wizard...

1261
01:54:43,840 --> 01:54:45,159
...get me out of here!

1262
01:54:45,400 --> 01:54:47,197
I got an old exit.
Wabash and Lake.

1263
01:54:51,080 --> 01:54:52,672
Oh, shit!

1264
01:55:12,640 --> 01:55:14,551
Help! Need a little help!

1265
01:55:16,120 --> 01:55:17,269
The door.

1266
01:55:32,600 --> 01:55:34,033
The door on your left.

1267
01:55:34,920 --> 01:55:36,114
Your other left!

1268
01:55:42,560 --> 01:55:43,754
The back door.

1269
01:56:03,680 --> 01:56:04,749
Oh, no.

1270
01:56:06,360 --> 01:56:07,793
Here they come.

1271
01:56:35,400 --> 01:56:36,594
He's going to make it.

1272
01:56:46,400 --> 01:56:49,392
The fire escape at the end
of the alley, room 303.

1273
01:57:22,880 --> 01:57:24,108
They' re inside.

1274
01:57:26,280 --> 01:57:27,349
Hurry, Neo.

1275
01:58:21,120 --> 01:58:22,348
It can't be.

1276
01:58:29,840 --> 01:58:31,159
Check him.

1277
01:58:35,000 --> 01:58:36,479
He's gone.

1278
01:58:42,920 --> 01:58:45,229
Goodbye, Mr. Anderson.

1279
01:58:54,920 --> 01:58:56,797
I' m not afraid anymore.

1280
01:58:58,360 --> 01:58:59,554
The Oracle told me...

1281
01:58:59,720 --> 01:59:04,999
...that I'd fall in love with that man.
The man that I love would be the One.

1282
01:59:08,000 --> 01:59:09,877
So you see...

1283
01:59:10,560 --> 01:59:12,471
...you can't be dead.

1284
01:59:14,000 --> 01:59:15,752
You can't be...

1285
01:59:17,240 --> 01:59:19,310
...because I love you.

1286
01:59:21,080 --> 01:59:22,718
You hear me?

1287
01:59:23,800 --> 01:59:25,392
I love you.

1288
01:59:48,360 --> 01:59:49,395
Now, get up.

1289
01:59:57,800 --> 01:59:58,835
No.

1290
02:00:24,240 --> 02:00:25,468
How?

1291
02:00:26,320 --> 02:00:27,309
He is the One.

1292
02:02:45,880 --> 02:02:47,518
I know you're out there.

1293
02:02:47,760 --> 02:02:49,512
I can feel you now.

1294
02:02:49,920 --> 02:02:51,638
I know that you're afraid.

1295
02:02:51,880 --> 02:02:53,393
You're afraid of us.

1296
02:02:53,720 --> 02:02:55,472
You 're afraid of change.

1297
02:02:56,640 --> 02:02:58,073
I don 't know the future.

1298
02:02:58,320 --> 02:03:00,788
I didn 't come here to tell you
how this is going to end.

1299
02:03:01,040 --> 02:03:03,873
I came here to tell you
how it's going to begin.

1300
02:03:04,800 --> 02:03:06,313
I'll hang up this phone.

1301
02:03:06,560 --> 02:03:09,518
And then I'll show these people
what you don 't want them to see.

1302
02:03:09,760 --> 02:03:11,557
I'm going to show them a world...

1303
02:03:11,800 --> 02:03:13,472
... without you.

1304
02:03:13,760 --> 02:03:17,230
A world without rules and controls,
without borders or boundaries.

1305
02:03:17,480 --> 02:03:21,029
A world where anything is possible.

1306
02:03:23,560 --> 02:03:24,834
Where we go from there...

1307
02:03:25,080 --> 02:03:26,957
...is a choice I leave to you.